@quantumkitty - The internet tends to expose us to the very best and the very worst of what's out there because what's in the middle just doesn't generate clicks. It gives a very distorted sense of the world - every content creator out there is going to present to you their view of the world, hyper-concentrated for your rapid consumption.

You've got to have your own goals because working towards your own ends is the only way you're going to get any sense of agency in this world - you have to shape the world that is *local* to you, and not get trapped in the despair of events occurring far away that you're powerless to change.

Have a purpose in life. Steer your life. Change it for the better. People who have no self-agency are in no position to be meddling in the affairs of the world anyways. Don't obsess over things you have no control over - just prepare for them.
